Hybrid Book Recommendation System :

A Python-based book recommendation system that combines K-Means clustering and Collaborative Filtering to provide personalized book suggestions. This hybrid approach leverages both user preferences and book features to enhance recommendation accuracy.

Features :

User-Based Collaborative Filtering: Suggests books based on similar user preferences.

K-Means Clustering: Groups users with similar reading patterns for more precise recommendations.

Hybrid Recommendation: Combines clustering and collaborative filtering for improved personalization.

Interactive: Users can input their favorite books and get tailored suggestions.

Scalable: Works efficiently with large datasets of books and user ratings.

HOW IT WORKS? 

Data Preprocessing: Cleans and structures the dataset.

Clustering Users: Applies K-Means clustering to group users with similar tastes.

Collaborative Filtering: Computes recommendations based on user similarity within clusters.

Hybrid Recommendation: Combines the strengths of clustering and collaborative filtering to suggest books.
